{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17649957","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17649957"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T21:08:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T21:08:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18384"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18384","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18384"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.94,0,0,0.06,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11102"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80436"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11102","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11102"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18384"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65723"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"260"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1432"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5810"},{"type":"tags","id":"9511"},{"type":"tags","id":"10223"},{"type":"tags","id":"11229"},{"type":"tags","id":"11318"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25741"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25743"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80436","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80436"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old male presents with an acutely swollen knee with pain, inability to weight bear and fever.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is a potential principle of treatment for acute septic arthritis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Joint aspiration with antimicrobial therapy","Corticosteroid injection into the joint","Immobilisation for two weeks","Antibiotics without joint aspiration","Aspirin administration only"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EJoint aspiration with antibiotic therapy\u003C/strong\u003E is the appropriate initial management of septic arthritis. Joint aspiration helps reduce bacterial load, by directly removing purulent material and inflammatory mediators, as well as providing synovial fluid samples for Gram stain, culture, and sensitivity testing to guide antibiotic therapy. Systemic antibiotics are given to target the infection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECorticosteroid injection into the joint\u003C/strong\u003E is contraindicated in septic arthritis as it may worsen the infection by suppressing local immune response.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImmobilisation for two weeks\u003C/strong\u003E alone is not appropriate as it does not address the underlying infection and thus can lead to joint stiffness, loss of function and poorer outcomes.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAntibiotics without joint aspiration\u003C/strong\u003E is inadequate as purulent material needs to be removed to reduce bacterial load and inflammatory mediators, it is also imperative in directing antimicrobial therapy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAspirin administration only\u003C/strong\u003E is insufficient as it only addresses pain and inflammation without treating the infection or removing purulent material.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EProper management of septic arthritis requires a combination of appropriate systemic antibiotics and adequate joint drainage to prevent joint destruction. Joint aspiration is a key component of septic arthritis management to remove purulent material and reduce bacterial load, as well as to assist in directed antimicrobial therapy. Early treatment of septic arthritis is crucial to prevent joint destruction. Systemic antibiotics combined with joint drainage are the cornerstones of septic arthritis treatment.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Joint lavage is a key component of septic arthritis management to remove purulent material and reduce bacterial load.","Corticosteroid injections are contraindicated in septic arthritis as they may worsen infection by suppressing local immune response.","Early diagnosis and treatment of septic arthritis through joint aspiration and antibiotics is crucial to prevent permanent joint destruction."],"references":["Patton, K. T., \u0026 Thibodeau, G. A. (2018). Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book: Anthony\u0027s Textbook of Anatomy \u0026 Physiology-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Ombregt, L. (2013). A System of Orthopaedic Medicine-E-Book: A System of Orthopaedic Medicine-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences.","Sud, A., \u0026 Ranjan, R. (2021). Textbook of Orthopaedics, 2e-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Dandy, D. J., \u0026 Edwards, D. J. (2009). Essential Orthopaedics and Trauma E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Momodu II, Savaliya V. Septic arthritis. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2025 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538176/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65723"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18384"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65723","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65723"},"attributes"